t.test(spotdata200$popularity,spotdata200$explicit)

##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  spotdata200$popularity and spotdata200$explicit
## t = 261.32, df = 1624.4, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  67.36264 68.38149
## sample estimates:
##  mean of x  mean of y 
## 68.3275649  0.4555006

## Call:

## popularity   0.01815    0.00493   3.682 0.000232 ***

## 
## (Dispersion parameter for binomial family taken to be 1)
## 
##     Null deviance: 2230.2  on 1617  degrees of freedom

spotdata200%>%
  ggplot(aes(x = explicit,popularity, group=explicit, fill= factor(explicit)))+
  scale_fill_discrete(labels = c("No", "Yes"))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  geom_jitter(shape=16, position=position_jitter(0.05), alpha=1/10)+
  theme_dark()+
  theme(legend.background = element_rect(fill = "darkgray"))+
  labs(x="Explicit",y="Popularity", title="Does Explicit Content Effect Popularity?", fill =  "Explicit")

spotdata200%>%
  ggplot(aes(x=popularity,y=explicit))+
  geom_point()+
  stat_smooth(method = glm ,method.args = list(family= "binomial"))+
  labs(x="Explicit Content", y="Popularity", title="GLM of Explicit Variable")
